The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, May 20, 2004 				 NDTV makes dazzling debut
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, May 19: New Delhi Television Ltd (NDTV) made a sparkling debut on the bourses with its shares closing at a 42 per cent gain from its offer price of Rs 70. 																								The shares of the Prannoy Roy and Radhika Roy-promoted company closed at Rs 99.40 on volatile trading. The listing of the NDTV scrip was delayed by a day from Tuesday after the market mayhem on Monday.																								The first trade for one share was struck at Rs 100. The NDTV scrip rose to an intra-day high of Rs 124.85 in early trades, but declined to a low of Rs 76.65 before bargain hunting saw the share recovering. 
